/-!
# An independent normal form for the exact centered `SU(2)` trace algebra

This module constructs the independent-basis workaround left open by the
Cayley--Hamilton non-descent result.  Its scope is exact and deliberately
explicit: it is the full polynomial trace-word algebra generated by the
centered fundamental and twice-wound trace of one actual block plaquette.
It is not the unenumerated continuum `F,D` operator quotient claimed in v14.

For `SU(2)`, the exact relation `b = 4a - a²` reduces every generated trace
word to a unique polynomial in `a`.  Uniqueness is semantic, not syntactic:
an explicit infinite Cayley-rotation family of actual `SU(2)` matrices proves
that distinct normal polynomials define distinct evaluated functions.  Thus
the evaluated quotient is exactly the one-variable polynomial algebra.

Since `a` has construction-derived canonical dimension four, the transversal
basis through dimension sixteen is `1,a,a²,a³,a⁴`.  Its coefficient duals are
exactly biorthogonal, and normal-form coordinate truncation is well-defined by
construction.  This decides the independent-basis repair on the trace algebra
that carries the MOVE-3 Cayley--Hamilton obstruction; transfer to v14's much
larger `F,D` catalog remains a separate obligation.
-/

set_option autoImplicit false

noncomputable section

open scoped BigOperators Matrix.Norms.Elementwise Polynomial

namespace Mettapedia
namespace QuantumTheory
namespace YangMills
namespace SU2IndependentTraceBasis

open SU2WilsonBlockPilot
open SU2CayleyHamiltonTruncationObstruction
